      <h4>1. <strong>Respiratory Issues:</strong></h4>
      <p>- <strong>Inhalation of Smoke and Fumes:</strong> Cooking generates smoke, grease particles, and combustion
        by-products like carbon monoxide and nitrogen dioxide. Inhaling these can irritate the respiratory system and
        exacerbate conditions such as asthma and bronchitis.</p>
      <p>- <strong>Allergies:</strong> Poor ventilation can lead to a buildup of allergens like dust, mold spores, and pet
